-- MOVES-PineBridge Investments names John Thornton non-exec chairman
-- 
-- Thu Nov 06, 2014 11:46AM EST
-- None



Nov 6 (Reuters) - Asset manager PineBridge Investments said it named John Thornton as non-executive chairman, effective Nov. 21.

Thornton succeeds E. Mervyn Davies, who presided over the board for four years. Thornton, who retired in 2003 as president and member of the board of Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N>, is a professor at Tsinghua University School of Economics and Management in Beijing.